*tar-1.23-r4 (27 Oct 2011)

  27 Oct 2011; Mickaël Salaün <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.23-r4.ebuild, -tar-1.23-r3.ebuild:
  Remove the unpack/cd to effectively apply the strncpy patch needed by
  gcc-4.5 to prevent buffer overflow.

*tar-1.23-r3 (19 Jul 2010)

  19 Jul 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.23-r3.ebuild, -tar-1.22.ebuild,
  -files/tar-1.21-revert-pipe.patch, +files/tar-1.23-revert-pipe.patch,
  +files/tar-1.23-strncpy.patch, +files/tar-1.23-symlink-k-hang.patch,
  +files/tar-1.23-tests.patch, files/tar.1:
  Bump to latest, fix for CVE-2010-0624.

*tar-1.22 (03 Mar 2010)

  03 Mar 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.22.ebuild, -tar-1.19-r2.ebuild,
  -files/tar-1.19-gnu-inline.patch, -files/tar-1.19-update-flag.patch,
  +files/tar-1.21-revert-pipe.patch:
  Bump to latest. Install everything in /usr if USE clip-rm is set, so
  that sharing will be automatic between all views.

  20 Apr 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  tar-1.19-r2.ebuild:
  Switch to verictl2.eclass.

*tar-1.19-r2 (16 Jul 2008)

  16 Jul 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.19-r2.ebuild, -tar-1.19-r1.ebuild:
  Switch to CCSD veriexec hashes.

*tar-1.19-r1 (26 Apr 2007)

  26 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.19-r1.ebuild, -tar-1.16.1-r1.ebuild, 
  +files/tar-1.19-gnu-inline.patch, +files/tar-1.19-update-flag.patch:
  Bump to latest *unstable* tar to fix GLSA-200709-09 and compilation
  issues with glibc-2.6. This is taken from gentoo's ~x86 and marked x86
  because the latest gentoo stable version has issues with ark (see gentoo
  bug #200315.
  Changeset is the same as 1.16.1-r1, except that CAP_MKNOD is only given to
  tar in CLIP core, not in RM.

*tar-1.16.1-r1 (26 Apr 2007)

  26 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +tar-1.16.1-r1.ebuild, -tar-1.16.1.ebuild:
  Add IUSE clip-rm to install a copy of tar in /user_root/bin, to 
  provide the USER view with an ark-compatible tar.

  07 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  -tar-1.15.1.ebuild:
  Remove stale ebuild.

*tar-1.16.1 (26 Apr 2007)

  26 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  tar-1.16.1.ebuild:
  Initial CLIP import, add verictl support providing an authorized
  CAP_SYS_MKNOD for /bin/tar, needed for the new (u)mount.crypt.
